---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const title = "EF Classroom - Alexis Morin";
---

<Base title={title}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/classroom.css" />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="body-img bdimg-classroom"></div>

  <div id="intro">
    <h3 class="tagline mobile-glass">
      EF Classroom - Research, UX &amp; UI Design
    </h3>
  </div>

  <div class="content" id="classroomintro">
    <section>
      <div class="col-md-12 center">
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <h3 style="font-weight:300;">The EF Classroom</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <p>
            EF prides itself in bringing real teachers into the English-language
            education of students all over the world. A cornerstone of this
            experience is the Online Classroom.
          </p>
          <p>
            Already deeply involved with a generic Adobe Connect&trade; and its
            proprietary Flash technology, EF needed to make a change. In a bold
            move, EF decided to build and deploy its own multi-user interactive
            classroom, including the voice and video communication.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content contribution">
    <section>
      <div class="col-xs-12 center">
        <p>
          My contribution to the project was to:
          <ul style="list-style-type:circle; margin-left: 20px;">
            <li>
              plan the project lifecycle (scope, strategy, design, development,
              testing, rollout, launch),
            </li>
            <li>initial definition of problem-space and user research,</li>
            <li>
              design the students' UX for 3 platforms (web, tablet, mobile),
            </li>
            <li>design the teachers' UX for web,</li>
            <li>build interactive prototypes aimed at user-research,</li>
            <li>perform user research and design validation in Mandarin,</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="am-bold">Company:</span> EF Education First (Shanghai, China)<br
          />
          <span class="am-bold">Team:</span> Lilith Lin, Chriest Yu, Chris Chen<br
          />
          <span class="am-bold">Role:</span> User Experience Designer<br />
          <span class="am-bold">Timeline:</span> October 2014 to July 2015<br />
          <span class="am-bold">Status:</span> EF Classroom is available on Google
          Play and the Apple App Store.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a
            href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ef.evc2015"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block; margin-right: 10px;"
          >
            <img
              src="/images/googlePlay.png"
              width="151"
              alt="EF Classroom on Google Play"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/ef-classroom/id1062473985?mt=8"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
            style="display: inline-block;"
          >
            <img
              src="/images/appStore.png"
              width="151"
              alt="EF Classroom on the App Store"
            />
          </a>
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/classroom-casestudy"
            >View the case-study of a project on student churn of the previous
            EF Classroom.</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-12 center">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <img
            src="/images/projects/classroom/ipad-notes.jpg"
            width="100%"
            alt="Notes allows students to record notes during class"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <img
            src="/images/projects/classroom/ipad-chat.jpg"
            width="100%"
            alt="Chat allows text communication between students and the teacher"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-12 center">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <img
            src="/images/projects/classroom/ipad-attendees.jpg"
            width="100%"
            alt="Attendees panel shows who is in the class"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <img
            src="/images/projects/classroom/ipad-info.jpg"
            width="100%"
            alt="Info displays metadata about the class"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-xs-12 center">
        <div class="col-md-6 padding-xs">
          <h4>Teacher Observation</h4>
          <p>
            <img
              src="/images/projects/classroom/teacher-observation.jpg"
              width="100%"
              alt="Photo of an EF teacher teaching from a teaching center in Shanghai, China"
            />
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 padding-xs">
          <h4>Bespoke Features</h4>
          <ul class="teacherfeatures">
            <li>
              <img
                src="/images/projects/classroom/raisehand.png"
                alt="icon for raising your hand"
              />
              Class Management
            </li>
            <li>
              <img
                src="/images/projects/classroom/slides.png"
                alt="icon for class slides"
              />
              Tailored Teaching Content
            </li>
            <li>
              <img
                src="/images/projects/classroom/mutedmic.png"
                alt="icon for a muted microphone"
              />
              Microphone Rights Control
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content" id="teacherteaching">
    <section>
      <h4>Students can learn anywhere, at their convenience.</h4>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <div class="col-xs-12 center">
        <div class="col-xs-12 padding-no center">
          <h3 style="font-weight:300;">Consistent Across The Board</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-2">
          <h4>Icons</h4>
          <p>Unique, tailor-made, cross-device, and readable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-10">
          <img
            src="/images/projects/classroom/classroom-icons@2x.jpg"
            alt="12 stylish icons which were designed for the EF Classroom"
            style="width:100%;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="content" id="classroom-isometric">
    <section>
      <h4>Fully featured, even on touch devices!</h4>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
